To Ed,<br>
First of all, how do you know my perspective on the Vietnam war or my fathers view?  Second of all, pal, my name is not junior, my name is posted there so take a look.  I'm not taking sides with Spatz.  I respect deeply the Nam vet and have had my run ins with him as well.  I just recently defended the Nam vet image on the Winter Soldier string.<br><br>
First of all pal, I deeply respect Native American views (I have taught them to students), but I'm sorry your voice is no louder than mine warrior or not.  So cut the Warrior first attitude pal.  My father defended this country and I've supported it too.  Your not the only one entitled to talk.  This is not a Indian Nation, built on Warrior codes, but a Nation of all Americans, of all races, beliefs, creeds, religions etc.  If you went into the service to defend your country, you would appreciate that.  Killing the enemy doesn't give you a special pass.   NO, I'm not a Commie, or a anti-war character-I helped defend the &quot;warrior image&quot; on one thread here.  I've seen the pain of Vietnam in many vets I help, I've seen Vietnam in my father, I've seen pain in families who lost someone and in people who lost friends-THAT GIVES ME THE RIGHT TO SPEAK.  IF YOU DON&quot;T LIKE THAT TOUGH LUCK!!!!  This is America, we have a freedom to speech.  Besides, YOU DON&quot;T EVEN KNOW ME. YOU JUDGE SOMEONE YOU DON&quot;T KNOW.  That is what the anti-war protestor did to the vet.  I try to repect Nam vets, but you make it hard.  Go ahead and say what you like, I will speak and say what I want to say.  Forget about exclusive clubs, if you want that start tour own website-THIS IS A PUBLIC FORUM!!!-Open to all!!  
<p><code>--   (Joe) </code><p>


